The paper deals with a problem of path planning for robots to learn a spatial field in minimum time. This problem is related to robotics (cs.RO) as it involves the use of robots. The use of Gaussian Process regression also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The problem of path planning can also be seen as a control problem, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the mathematical optimization (cs.MA) sub-category.
